<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870520-0030 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Microcom Inc.</HL><DD> 05/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MNPIINITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   MICROCOM INC., sold one million common shares at $17 each in an intial offering yesterday, according to lead underwriter Salomon Brothers Inc. The company sold 800,000 shares and shareholders the remainder. Proceeds to the company will be used for general purposes. Microcom, which is based in Norwood, Mass., makes and markets software enhanced communications equipment for high-speed, error-free telephone transmission of data. In over-the-counter trading yesterday, the company's shares closed at $17.25. </TEXT></DOC>